From c413cbc70785efff20b86b3bbc68b85a10c42e7d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Josh Law <joshlaw48@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 11 Apr 2026 20:22:16 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] lib/ts_fsm: Remove overzealous end-of-data check

The FSM text search was incorrectly dropping valid matches if they were
followed by trailing data in the search window. This was due to an
unnecessary end_of_data() check that demanded the match conclude
exactly at the window boundary.

Remove this check to ensure patterns are correctly identified regardless
of their position relative to the end of the input stream.

Signed-off-by: Josh Law <joshlaw48@gmail.com>
---
 lib/ts_fsm.c | 3 +--
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/lib/ts_fsm.c b/lib/ts_fsm.c
index 8450e6316fa4..60c2903918e5 100644
--- a/lib/ts_fsm.c
+++ b/lib/ts_fsm.c
@@ -247,8 +247,7 @@ static unsigned int fsm_find(struct ts_config *conf, struct ts_state *state)
 		block_idx++;
 	}
 
-	if (end_of_data())
-		goto found_match;
+	goto found_match;
 
 no_match:
 	return UINT_MAX;
-- 
2.43.0

